<HEADLINE>
FT  16 JUL 93 / Arts: Today's Television
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER DUNKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The 1993 Promenade Concert season opens with a performance of Richard
Strauss' one act opera 'Elektra', performed by the BBC Symphony Orchestra
and the BBC Singers under conductor Andrew Davis, relayed live from the
Royal Albert Hall and broadcast simultaneously on BBC2 and Radio 3. Soprano
Marilyn Zschau is Elektra, mezzo soprano Eva Randova is Clytemnestra,
Willard White sings the part of Orestes, and William Cochran is Aegisthus
(7.30).
Herbal medicine is the subject of the new series Blooming Bellamy. Biologist
David Bellamy shows that herbs used for centuries in preparing medicines can
be found in such banal spots as the pavements of south London and on railway
stations (7.30 BBC1).
It is a good night for lovers of the kitsch and the odd in popular music.
BBC2's series of Rock Docs offers a 1974 documentary 'On Tour With The
Osmonds' and Channel 4 shows the Marc Bolan documentary 'The Legendary
Years' (12.45, as part of its 'Dinomania' round-up, Bolan's band being
called T Rex).
