FT  16 JUL 93 / Parliament and Politics: Gulf war costs put at Pounds 2,345m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MR Michael Portillo, chief secretary to the Treasury, told the Commons
yesterday that the latest estimate of the additional military cost of the
Gulf conflict, spread over several years, was Pounds 2,345m.
By the end of March the Export Credits Guarantee Department had paid Pounds
499m of claims arising from the situation in the Gulf in 1990-91 and which
had yet to be recovered.
Mr Portillo said that a further Pounds 160m of claims on Iraq had yet to be
examined, and other departments had incurred minor costs. The 'bulk of these
costs' had been offset by the cash contributions from other governments
totalling Pounds 2,049m.
