<TEXT>
MR Norman Lamont, still smarting after his dismissal from the Treasury,
discomforted the prime minister and delighted the opposition benches in the
Commons yesterday by highlighting the success of the policies with which he
was associated as chancellor, Ivor Owen writes.
Labour MPs did their utmost to underline Mr John Major's embarrassment as Mr
