to congratulate Mr Kenneth Clarke, his successor as chancellor 'on the rapid
success of his policies'.
The House was convulsed in glee, with even Mr Clarke, on the government
front bench, grinning broadly.
Mr Major replied: 'I know the chancellor will be most grateful for your
support of his policies'.
