<HEADLINE>
FT  16 JUL 93 / Aspin orders military support to the Adriatic
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GEORGE GRAHAM
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Les Aspin, US defence secretary, has ordered 30 ground attack and 10
support aircraft to the Adriatic to spearhead Nato's plan to provide aerial
protection for United Nations peacekeepers in Bosnia, writes George Graham
in Washington. According to the Pentagon they will include A-10 ground
attack aircraft, F/A-18 Hornet jet fighters and AC-130s, a gunship version
of the C-130 transport.
France, the Netherlands and Britain are also sending aircraft to take part
in the Nato air umbrella. Nato this week approved the mission from July 22,
but plans have been referred to the UN for approval and a decision on
timing.
