   ISLAMABAD
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Widespread flood damage was feared in Pakistan last night as another 100
villages were flooded in the province of Punjab by the rivers Ravi and
Chenab, adding to the 250 already affected, Farhan Bokhari reports from
Islamabad.
The floods have again raised fears of large-scale destruction to crops and
property.
</TEXT>
