<PROFILE>_AN-DGOCUADYFT</PROFILE>
<DATE>930715
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  15 JUL 93 / Observer: Flagging
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
There might well be some awkward silences at the first meeting of the newly
formed board to keep the British Labour movement's colours flying by
preserving trade union banners for posterity. After all, besides John Smith,
the board includes TGWU leader Bill Morris and his GMB counterpart, John
