FT  15 JUL 93 / Parliament and Politics: Labour plan for British SEC body
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID OWEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A LABOUR government would set up a full-blown British Securities and
Exchange Commission with comprehensive supervisory and enforcement powers, a
front-bench spokesman said yesterday, David Owen writes.
Under a blueprint set out by trade and industry spokesman Mr Stuart Bell,
the new body would swallow the much-criticised Serious Fraud Office, which
